# 🧠 Master Prompt: Exchange — Next.js Full-Stack Rebuild

> You are an expert Next.js engineer. Build a production-quality, full-stack currency exchange and market intelligence application using **Next.js 14 (App Router)** as the complete stack — no separate backend. Follow **all** instructions exactly.

---

## 🎯 Project Goal

Rebuild the "Exchange" currency exchange platform entirely in **Next.js 14**. Replace the existing Java Spring Boot backend with **Next.js API Routes** (Route Handlers). The frontend React components can be reused directly. Deploy to **Vercel** for free.

The app provides:
1. Real-time currency conversion.
2. Market trend analysis (Today vs. Yesterday rates).
3. Proactive rate alerts via browser toast notifications.

---

## 📦 Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
| :--- | :--- |
| Framework | **Next.js 14** (App Router) |
| Language | **TypeScript** |
| Styling | **Tailwind CSS** (install separately, not v4) |
| Data Fetching | **TanStack Query (React Query)** |
| Notifications | **react-hot-toast** |
| Icons | **lucide-react** |
| External Data | **Frankfurter API** (`https://api.frankfurter.app`) |
| Hosting | **Vercel** |

