## 🎨 Design System & Aesthetics

This is a **luxury fintech dark mode** application. The visual standard is extremely high.

- **Background**: Deep navy `#020617` (not pure black).
- **Glass Panels**: Use `backdrop-blur`, semi-transparent `bg-white/5` or `bg-white/10` with `border border-white/10` and `rounded-2xl`.
- **Brand Colors**:
  - Primary: Indigo/Violet (`#6366f1`)
  - Accent: Pink/Magenta (`#ec4899`)
  - Success: Green (`#22c55e`)
  - Warning: Amber (`#f59e0b`)
- **Typography**: Use **Inter** from Google Fonts via `next/font/google`.
- **Background Orbs**: Add two large blurred `div` circles (`rounded-full blur-[140px] pointer-events-none`) in brand-primary and brand-accent at 10% opacity as decorative elements.
- **Animations**: Implement CSS `@keyframes` for:
  - `animate-float`: Subtle vertical bobbing on the header.
  - `animate-shine`: Gradient text shift on the `<h1>` title.
  - `animate-pulse` / skeleton: Use Tailwind's built-in `animate-pulse` for loading states.

---

## 🧩 Component Specifications

### `<ExchangeCard />`
The primary conversion interface.
- Inputs: Amount (number input), "From" currency (CurrencySelector), "To" currency (CurrencySelector).
- Swap button (⇌ icon): Swaps the `from` and [to](file:///c:/Users/yoeth/Documents/exchange/exchange/frontend/exchange-frontend/src/components/AlertSettingsCard.tsx#37-43) currencies.
- Input is debounced (500ms) before triggering a fetch.
- Amount input shows the `from` currency flag and code inside the input on the right side.
- Uses [useConversion](file:///c:/Users/yoeth/Documents/exchange/exchange/frontend/exchange-frontend/src/hooks/useExchange.ts#18-30) hook for data.
- Shows `<ExchangeResult />` below.

### `<CurrencySelector />`
A custom-styled searchable dropdown to select a currency.
- Displays a **country flag** (from `https://flagcdn.com/w40/{countryCode}.png`) next to currency code and name.
- Has an integrated search input.
- Both the trigger button AND each dropdown item show the flag.
- Dropdown background must be **fully opaque** and dark: use `bg-[#0f172a]` with `border border-white/20`, `rounded-2xl`, and a large `box-shadow`.

### `<ExchangeResult />`
Displays the conversion output.
- Show: `"{amount} {from} = {convertedAmount} {to}"` using proper locale formatting (`Intl.NumberFormat`).
- Show the exchange rate: `"1 {from} = {rate} {to}"`.
- Show the data date.

### `<ComparisonTable />`
Displays trend data for the current currency pair.
- Fetches from [useComparison](file:///c:/Users/yoeth/Documents/exchange/exchange/frontend/exchange-frontend/src/hooks/useExchange.ts#31-41) hook.
- Shows current rate, previous rate, absolute change, percentage change.
- Uses `<TrendBadge />` to display trend direction.

### `<TrendBadge />`
Renders a colored pill badge for a [TrendDirection](file:///c:/Users/yoeth/Documents/exchange/exchange/frontend/exchange-frontend/src/types/exchange.ts#3-4).
- `UP`: green, upward arrow icon.
- `DOWN`: red, downward arrow icon.
- `STABLE`: gray, minus/dash icon.
- All from lucide-react.

### `<AlertSettingsCard />`
Lets user set a rate alert target.
- Inputs: Target rate, direction (`ABOVE` / `BELOW`).
- Polling: Every 30 seconds via [useRateAlert](file:///c:/Users/yoeth/Documents/exchange/exchange/frontend/exchange-frontend/src/hooks/useRateAlert.tsx#6-70) hook.
- When the rate condition is met, fire a toast notification via `react-hot-toast`.
- Alert persists in `localStorage` so it survives page refresh.

### Loading Skeletons
Every component that fetches data must have an `animate-pulse` skeleton state. Use gray rounded rectangles to approximate the component's shape.

### Error States
Every component must handle fetch errors gracefully with a brief message and a "Retry" button.

